#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.96"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.96:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.96:0.2"
msgid "10. Saḷavagga "
msgstr "10. The Sixes "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.96:0.3"
msgid "96. Parihānadhammasutta "
msgstr "96. Liable to Decline "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.96:1.1"
msgid "“Parihānadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi aparihānadhammañca cha ca abhibhāyatanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you who is liable to decline, who is not liable to decline, and the six fields of mastery. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.96:1.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, parihānadhammo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is someone liable to decline? "

#. VAR: akusalā sarasaṅkappā → akusalā dhammā sarasaṅkappā (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.96:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees a sight with the eye, bad, unskillful phenomena arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

#. VAR: byantīkaroti → vyantī karoti (bj) | vyantikaroti (pts1) | byantiṃ karoti (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.96:1.5"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu adhivāseti nappajahati na vinodeti na byantīkaroti na anabhāvaṃ gameti, veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "Suppose that mendicant tolerates them and doesn’t give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them. They should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:1.6"
msgid "‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’. "
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are declining. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:1.7"
msgid "Parihānañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti … pe …. "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.77, sc2
msgctxt "sn35.96:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā uppajjanti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant hears a sound … smells an odor … tastes a flavor … feels a touch … "

msgctxt "sn35.96:2.2"
msgid "puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "knows a thought with the mind, bad, unskillful phenomena arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:2.3"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu adhivāseti nappajahati na vinodeti na byantīkaroti na anabhāvaṃ gameti, veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "If that mendicant tolerates them and doesn’t give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them, they should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:2.4"
msgid "‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’. "
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are declining. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:2.5"
msgid "Parihānañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti. "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.96:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, parihānadhammo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how someone is liable to decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.96:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, aparihānadhammo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is someone not liable to decline? "

msgctxt "sn35.96:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees a sight with the eye, bad, unskillful phenomena arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:3.3"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "Suppose that mendicant doesn’t tolerate them but gives them up, gets rid of them, eliminates them, and obliterates them. They should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:3.4"
msgid "‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’. "
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are not declining. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:3.5"
msgid "Aparihānañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti … pe …. "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.96:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā uppajjanti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant hears a sound … smells an odor … tastes a flavor … feels a touch … "

msgctxt "sn35.96:4.2"
msgid "puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "knows a thought with the mind, bad, unskillful phenomena arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:4.3"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "Suppose that mendicant doesn’t tolerate them but gives them up, gets rid of them, eliminates them, and obliterates them. They should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:4.4"
msgid "‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’. "
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are not declining. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:4.5"
msgid "Aparihānañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti. "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.96:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aparihānadhammo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how someone is not liable to decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.96:5.1"
msgid "Katamāni ca, bhikkhave, cha abhibhāyatanāni? "
msgstr "And what are the six fields of mastery? "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā nuppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees a sight with the eye, bad, unskillful phenomena don’t arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.3"
msgid "Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "They should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.4"
msgid "‘abhibhūtametaṃ āyatanaṃ’. "
msgstr "‘This sense field has been mastered. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.5"
msgid "Abhibhāyatanañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti … pe … "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls a field of mastery.’ … "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.6"
msgid "puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya nuppajjanti pāpakā akusalā dhammā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant knows a thought with the mind, bad, unskillful phenomena don’t arise: memories and thoughts prone to fetters. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.7"
msgid "Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā: "
msgstr "They should understand: "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.8"
msgid "‘abhibhūtametaṃ āyatanaṃ’. "
msgstr "‘This sense field has been mastered. "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.9"
msgid "Abhibhāyatanañhetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatāti. "
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls a field of mastery.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.96:5.10"
msgid "Imāni vuccanti, bhikkhave, cha abhibhāyatanānī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the six fields of mastery.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.96:5.11"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

